# Auth module context. Security-critical with locked contracts.

version: 1

summary: |
  Authentication and authorization module. Handles JWT token
  issuance, validation, refresh, and role-based access control.
  Security-critical: all changes should be reviewed by the
  security team.

key_files:
  - path: middleware.ts
    why: "Express middleware that validates JWT on every API request."
    tags: [auth, middleware, jwt, security]
    verified_at: "d4e5f6a"
    locked: true
    owner: security

contracts:
  - name: "auth-security-contract"
    scope:
      paths: ["*.ts"]
      tags: [auth, security]
    content: |
      AUTH SECURITY REQUIREMENTS:
      1. Passwords MUST be hashed with bcrypt, cost factor 12.
      2. JWT access tokens expire after 15 minutes.
      3. Refresh tokens expire after 7 days and are single-use.
      4. Failed login attempts are rate-limited: 5 per minute per IP.
      5. All auth events MUST be logged to the audit trail.
      6. Token comparison MUST use constant-time comparison.
      7. Never log raw tokens, passwords, or secrets.
    verified_at: "d4e5f6a"
    locked: true
    owner: security

gotchas:
  - text: |
      The JWT_SECRET environment variable must be at least 256 bits.
      Shorter secrets will cause the server to reject all tokens
      with a cryptic "invalid signature" error. Check .env.example
      for the expected format.
    tags: [jwt, config, security]
    verified_at: "d4e5f6a"
    locked: false

tags: [auth, security, jwt]
